choices.text:
I am not a prime number.
I am between 20 and 40.
I am one more than a square number.
What number am I?
The number is 36. It meets the conditions that it is not a prime number, lies between 20 and 40, and is one more than a square number (i.e., 9 + 1 = 10). Therefore, the only possible answer is 36.
